args: You there! Gimme all your money!
You should stop pretending to be a thief.
...We? Ah. I see. You're not alone.\nWell, go round up whoever is with\nyou and bring them along.
Are you gonna turn us in?!
No. I have something else in mind.
Have you found more children, Alex?
Yes, and I think they're extra hungry.
I'll get to work right away.
We're making food for children like you\nwho have nowhere to go.
There's more where this came from,\nso eat heartily.
Aw, hell yeah! Look at all the grub!
Uh oh! It's the greedy fiends,\nRanzal and Luca! Let's get 'em!
They're too strong! They got us! Noooo!
Playing with some children who live\nat the local orphanage.
Oh! You're the girl who gave me\nthat paper crane.
I'm glad to see you're doing well.
Is this also made from a letter?
Hee hee! Don't read it until I'm gone, 'kay?\nIt's embarrassing.
Say, why don't you go play with the\nother children now that you're here?
Yaaaaay! Come on, let's go play!
The orphanage's matron has come\nto see you, Alex.
Thank you so much for always\nplaying with the children.
I'm happy to help. But there is something\nI wanted to talk to you about...
Can I speak to you for a moment?
If you have nowhere else to go,\nwhy not stay at the orphanage?
I spoke to the matron earlier,\nand she agreed to take you both in.
So we don't need to be cold anymore?\nYaaaaaaaaay!
You sure this isn't a trick?\nThey aren't just gonna use us?
This orphanage genuinely cares about\nthe children in their charge.
I made sure of that personally.
But if anything or anyone ever DOES\nupset you, you can return to the castle.
I'll always be willing to help.
Why are you doing all this?
A long time ago, a friend said something\nthat stuck with me.
＂Every child is a blessing from the\ngoddess, and every life should be happy.＂
Woof! Playin' with these rug rats is\nharder than I thought.
But it was also super fun!\nRight, {player_name}?
Although it was hard to tell whether you\nor the orphans were the more childish.
Alex? If I may ask, what did the paper\ncrane message have to say?
Well, that's sweet. You're going to keep\ntrying to help children, I take it?
Of course. There are many out there in\nthe world who have no home of their own.
I'll do everything I can to help them—\nand in doing so, I will atone for the\nbloody sins of my past.
That will be my life from now on.
